    "discriminators": [
     "Small, bright and heavily damped: a collar, sheep or sleigh bell is tiny, so its pitch and spectral_centroid_hz are high and its decay_time_seconds_60db is far SHORTER than any other bell here — the strap and the animal's body damp the ring.",
     "It is worn on something moving, so it usually arrives as a repeated jingle (a rhythmic onset train) rather than a single deliberate strike. That combination — bright, short-ringing, repeated — separates it from BELLS-HANDBELL, which is bigger, darker and rung on purpose.",
     "BELLS-LARGE is the opposite extreme: low, and ringing for many seconds.",
     "Orchestral sleigh bells or a kit cowbell are MUSICAL-PERCUSSION / MUSICAL-SHAKEN."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "BELLHand",
