    "discriminators": [
     "The longest and most inharmonic ring in the whole taxonomy: a struck disc whose partials are so dense and so detuned that it barely reads as pitched at all — very high inharmonicity with LOW harmonicity, decaying over many seconds.",
     "A gong blooms. Energy migrates upward after the strike through nonlinear coupling, so spectral_centroid_slope_hz_per_second is positive; a cast bell (BELLS-LARGE) rings out with a flat or falling centroid. That bloom, plus the low harmonicity, is the real gong/bell boundary.",
     "Struck with a soft mallet, so the attack is slower than a metal clapper strike.",
     "UCS v8.2 redirects most musical gongs, tam-tams and singing bowls to MUSICAL-BELLS, so this is a shrinking category and text should be trusted over signal when the two disagree."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "MUSCBell",
     "MUSCPerc",
     "MUSCTnprc",
     "BELLLrg",
     "METLTonl",
     "BELLMisc"
    ]
