    "discriminators": [
     "The middle of the bell size ladder, and size is the only real axis: brighter and shorter-ringing than BELLS-LARGE, darker and longer-ringing than the tiny BELLS-ANIMAL. Rung by hand, so several clapper strikes usually appear in one file.",
     "Strong metallic inharmonicity is what makes any of these a bell and not a mallet instrument — MUSICAL-PERCUSSION TUNED bars (glockenspiel, marimba, vibraphone) are tuned to near-INTEGER harmonic ratios, so their inharmonicity is low. High inharmonicity plus a long ring is the archetypal bell.",
     "Handbell choirs and carillons were moved to MUSICAL-BELLS in v8.2; this is the dinner, school and service bell."
    ],
